## Vue SFC Conventions

### Script Setup

**Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`** — no Options API, no `defineComponent`.

```vue
<!-- app/components/users/UserCard.vue -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import type { User } from '~/types/user'

interface Props {
  user: User
  compact?: boolean
}

const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  compact: false,
})

const emit = defineEmits<{
  select: [user: User]
  delete: [id: number]
}>()

function handleSelect() {
  emit('select', props.user)
}
</script>

<template>
  <div class="user-card" :class="{ 'user-card--compact': compact }" @click="handleSelect">
    <span>{{ user.name }}</span>
  </div>
</template>
```

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component files | PascalCase | `UserCard.vue`, `AppButton.vue` |
| Page files | kebab-case | `user-detail.vue` |
| Composables | camelCase + `use` prefix | `useUsers.ts`, `useAuth.ts` |
| Pinia stores | camelCase + `use` prefix | `useUserStore.ts` |
| Variables / functions | camelCase | `userId`, `fetchUsers()` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_PAGE_SIZE` |
| Types / Interfaces | PascalCase | `User`, `UserCreateInput` |

### Props and Emits

- Define props with TypeScript generics — never use runtime validators alone
- Use `withDefaults` for optional props
- Use typed `defineEmits` generic syntax

```typescript
// Good
const props = withDefaults(defineProps<{ label: string; disabled?: boolean }>(), {
  disabled: false,
})

// Avoid — untyped
const props = defineProps(['label', 'disabled'])
```

