## Routing and Navigation

Nuxt uses file-based routing — no `router.ts` to maintain.

```
app/pages/users/index.vue     →  /users
app/pages/users/[id].vue      →  /users/:id
app/pages/users/[id]/edit.vue →  /users/:id/edit
```

Navigation in templates and scripts:

```vue
<template>
  <!-- Template navigation -->
  <NuxtLink to="/users">Back to users</NuxtLink>
  <NuxtLink :to="`/users/${user.id}`">View user</NuxtLink>
</template>

<script setup lang="ts">
// Programmatic navigation
await navigateTo('/users')
await navigateTo({ path: '/users', query: { page: 2 } })

// Current route
const route = useRoute()
const userId = route.params.id
</script>
```

Route middleware (client guards):

```typescript
// app/middleware/auth.ts
export default defineNuxtRouteMiddleware(() => {
  const authStore = useAuthStore()
  if (!authStore.isAuthenticated) return navigateTo('/login')
})
```

Apply to a page: `definePageMeta({ middleware: 'auth' })`

